Autonomous Robot Navigation Simulator 🚀

An advanced robotics-inspired simulation project built in Python demonstrating autonomous navigation, path planning, control systems, and real-time visualization.

Features
A* Pathfinding Algorithm
PID Motion Controller
Dynamic Obstacle Avoidance
Sensor Fusion Concepts
Real-Time Robot Simulation
Modular Scalable Architecture
Unit Testing Support
Tech Stack
Python
Matplotlib
Algorithms & Data Structures
Robotics Concepts
Control Systems
Simulation Engineering
Project Goals

This project was designed to simulate real-world autonomous robot navigation systems used in robotics, AI, and intelligent mobility applications.

The simulator demonstrates:

Efficient route planning
Autonomous movement control
Obstacle handling
Real-time system updates
Engineering-focused software design
Skills Demonstrated
Software Engineering
Robotics Algorithms
AI/ML Foundations
System Design
Problem Solving
Modular Architecture
Real-Time Simulation
